I"l<p>When trying to mount an NFS share on <em>MacOS</em> Finder, there might occur a generic <em>“Opereation not Permitted”</em> error.
To fix this problem on the client-side, the share has to be mounted from the command line wih the <code class="highlighter-rouge">-o resvport</code> option:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nb">sudo </span>mount_nfs <span class="nt">-o</span> resvport 192.168.1.200:/media/data /Volumes/data
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>To be able to mount the share in Finder, the server-side configuration has to be extended with the <code class="highlighter-rouge">insecure</code> option in <em>/etc/exports</em>:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/media/data 192.168.1.0/24(rw,insecure,...)
</code></pre></div></div>

